THE Congress of South African Trade Unions (Cosatu) has apologised unreservedly for the barrage of insults hurled at City of Johannesburg MMC for Public Safety Michael Sun, saying it does not condone racism or racial discrimination.At the Cosatu protest march against state capture and corruption last Wednesday, participants stopped outside the Johannesburg City Council to hand a memorandum to Mayor Herman Mashaba.The mayor was not available to come and sign the memorandum himself and sent Sun to stand in for him.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvWQq40iveUCh70QVzvIpxyjomEJs3AizKwAbvL3eIVVopTwRyIk4Se4p9pMUeJtPQPxYL6uZxwCc4Ew0_APPbWji_z1CNjZsIpi-_T5X3ex6XLu9rhQQ83gffJayOxmsjxVYZNwbT4x72CKoT9RtffVCfISWMM4NDAf_F_wbQZmSHN9C2g3TrCY3jLu3gStLieA4tFr5Rq-HMFDlEmA03-rHBmqof2aRgzFoj5frjEimikw_1ERPTlne3-ejy4efCQsn7JisNb_cqucL-aihsPvNDoV-A\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzM-s5zpXRiA1EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
